name: Honeycomb V3PO RESTCONF calls
description: Common mgmt operations on VPP core using Honeycomb REST interface

folders.name: ETH
folders.description: Example requests for management of Ethernet type interfaces

requests.name: Add loopback ifc - cfg
requests.description: create loop interface

requests.name: Delete loopback ifc - cfg
requests.description: delete loop interface intfc loop1

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Get
requests.description: This call returns data stored in honeycomb,to verify actual data stored by vpp, call vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Delete
requests.description: Verify this call by invoking vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Ip Neighbour Add
requests.description: This call doesnt have respective dump call,because of performance issues(dump for this can contain millions of entries). Data inserted throught this call can be verified by calling vppctl show ip fib|arp

requests.name: Add arp proxy range #1
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set ip arp proxy 1.1.1.1 - 1.1.1.10

Can be verified with

vppctl show ip arp

requests.name: Add arp proxy range #2
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set ip arp proxy 2.2.2.2 - 2.2.2.42

Can be verified with

vppctl show ip arp

requests.name: Enable proxy arp for local0
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set interface proxy-arp local0 enable

requests.name: Delete arp proxy range #1
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set ip arp del proxy 1.1.1.1 - 1.1.1.10

Can be verified with

vppctl show ip arp

requests.name: Delete arp proxy range #2
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set ip arp del proxy 2.2.2.2 - 2.2.2.42

Can be verified with

vppctl show ip arp

requests.name: Disable proxy arp for local0
requests.description:
Equivalent of

vppctl set interface proxy-arp local0 disable

requests.name: Enable GigabitEthernet0/9/0 interface - cfg
requests.description:
Enables GigabitEthernet0/9/0 interface. Equivalent vppctl command:

vppctl set in state GigabitEthernet0/9/0 up

Needed to enable sub interface.

To verify invoke:

vppctl show int

requests.name: Remove local0 from bridge domain
requests.description:
Removes l2 interconnection of bridge-based type from local0 interface.
Corresponds to the following VAT command:

vat# sw_interface_set_l2_bridge sw_if_index 0 bd_id 1 disable

Verification in VAT:

vat# bridge_domain_dump

requests.name: Modify vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:
Modifies vhost-user interface socket.
To verify invoke:

vppctl show vhost-user

requests.name: Set vrf id for local0 - cfg
List disabled interfaces - context
requests.description: List disabled interfaces (e.g. deleted vxlan tunnels)

requests.name: Show local0 - oper
requests.description: Shows local0 interface operational state

requests.name: Enable tag-rewrite push - cfg
requests.description:
Enables tag-rewrite push operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 push dot1q 123 456

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: List naming contexts - context
requests.description: List mapping context stored in context datastore

requests.name: Read port mirroring
requests.description: show span

requests.name: Delete L2 FIB entry
requests.description:
Removes L2 FIB entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl l2fib del aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff [bd_id]

To verify run:

vppctl show l2fib verbose

requests.name: Disable tag-rewrite - cfg
requests.description:
Disables tag-rewrite operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 disable

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Create bridge domain - cfg
requests.description:
Creates bridgfe domain. Corresponds to invoking:

vat#  bridge_domain_add_del bd_id [bd_id] learn 0 forward 0 uu-flood 0 flood 1 arp-term 0

To verify run:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Enable tag-rewrite translate 1-2 - cfg
requests.description:
Enables tag-rewrite translate 1-2 operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 translate 1-2 dot1q 111 222

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Add L2 FIB entry (forward)
requests.description:
Adds L2 FIB static entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl l2fib add aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff [bd_id] local0

To verify run:

vppctl show l2fib verbose

requests.name: Add sub interface - cfg
requests.description:
Adds sub interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl create sub GigabitEthernet0/9/0 1 dot1q 100 inner-dot1q any

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

requests.name: Show bridge domain - cfg
requests.description: Shows testBD bridge domain configuration.

requests.name: Set ipv4 local0 interface - cfg netmask
Set ipv4 for sub-interface - cfg
requests.description:
Correponds to the following command:

vppctl set interface ip address GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 1.2.3.4/8

To verify invoke:
vppctl show int

requests.name: Set local0 as unnumbered (use GigabitEthernet0/8/0)
requests.description:
Make local0 borrow ip from GigabiteEthernet0/8/0.
Equivalent of

set interface unnumbered local0 use GigabitEthernet0/8/0

Can be verified with

vppctl show interface address

requests.name: Delete vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:
Deletes vhost user interface.
Corresponding vpp CLI command:

vppctl delete vhost-user sw_if_index [index]

To verify invoke:

vppctl show vhost-user

or

vppctl show int

requests.name: Add vhost user ifc - cfg
requests.description:
Adds vhost-user interface.
Corresponsing vpp cli command:

create vhost-user socket /tmp/soc1 server

To verify invoke:

vppctl show vhost-user

or

vppctl show int

requests.name: List ifcs - cfg
requests.description: List ifcs - cfg

requests.name: Delete ARP termination table entry
requests.description:
Removes ARP termination termination entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vat# bd_ip_mac_add_del bd_id [bd_id] 1.2.3.4 aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff del

To verify run:

vppctl show bridge-domain 1 detail

requests.name: Add ARP termination table entry
requests.description:
Adds ARP termination termination entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vat# bd_ip_mac_add_del bd_id [bd_id] 1.2.3.4 aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff

To verify run:

vppctl show bridge-domain 1 detail

requests.name: Add local0 to bridge domain
requests.description:
Adds l2 interconnection of bridge-based type to local0 interface.
Corresponds to the following command:

vppctl set interface l2 bridge local0 [bd_id]

To verify invoke:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: List ACL contexts - context
requests.description: List mapping context for ACLs stored in context datastore

requests.name: Get interface cfg
requests.description: Shows configuration for GigabitEthernet0/8/0

requests.name: Get interface - oper
requests.description: Shows operational state for GigabitEthernet0/8/0

requests.name: Remove ipv4 from local0 interface - cfg
Show local0 - cfg
requests.description: Shows local0 interface configuration

requests.name: Add L2 FIB entry (filter)
requests.description:
Adds L2 FIB static entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl l2fib add 00:01:02:03:04:05 [bd_id] filter

To verify run:

vppctl show l2fib verbose

requests.name: Show bridge domain - oper
requests.description:
Shows testBD bridge domain operational state.
Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Add L2 FIB entry (static, forward)
requests.description:
Adds L2 FIB static entry. Corresponds to invoking:

vppctl l2fib add 11:22:33:44:55:66 [bd_id] local0 static

To verify run:

vppctl show l2fib verbose

requests.name: Set port mirroring local0 -> GigabiteEthernet0/8/0
requests.description: set span src local0 dst GigabiteEthernet0/8/0

requests.name: Enable GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 interface - cfg
requests.description:
Enables GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub interface. Equivalent vppctl command:

vppctl set in state GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 up

To enable sub interface, super interface should be enabled first.

To verify invoke:

vppctl show int

requests.name: Enable tag-rewrite pop 1 - cfg
requests.description:
Enables tag-rewrite pop 1 operation for GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 sub-interface. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 tag-rewrite GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 pop 1

To verify run:
./build-root/install-vpp-native/vpp-api-test/bin/vpp_api_test json
and invoke:

#vat sw_interface_dump

or if sub-interface was added to bridge domain:

vppctl show bridge-domain [bd_id] detail

requests.name: Add sub interface to bridge-domain
requests.description:
Adds sub interface to bridge domain. Corresponsing vpp cli command:

vppctl set interface l2 bridge GigabitEthernet0/9/0.1 1 1

To verify invoke:
vppctl show bridge-domain 1 detail
